    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of velocipede generally intended for children, the body of which appears in the shape of a horse's body. Tricycle horses appeared in the mid 19th century and wheels of early examples were usually made of wood but during the 1860s these were superseded by metal spokes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
